Falling in love with who I am… 2023 was a roller coaster for me. A lot of traumatic changes, ups and downs, stepping out of my comfort zone, leaving things/people behind that no longer were for me. My whole world was flipped turned upside down. So many times I’ve heard “Naisha idk how you do it” so many people couldn’t understand how strong I was and didn’t break. They just couldn’t grasp the fact of how I was able to remain positive and still show the love & grace that wasn’t given to me. 1 thing I’ve always taken pride in, is the type of person I am. In life you will be tested on many levels..but how u react and handle those things/ situations will dictate YOUR outcome. God made me a promise to ask for the things I wanted & to leave behind what didn’t serve me, so that I can get everything I deserve. God has always been so amazing to me & I’m so grateful for all the transformations I’ve been through. As I continue to level up mentally, physically & spiritually the more things I’m able to manifest in my life. I’m vibrating on such an amazing level right now & I can’t wait to see what else he has in store for me this year. 🙏🏼❤️
